item.description: <!DOCTYPE html> Project 3 Predicting Car Crash Injury Severity Using Naive Bayes Classification¶ In this tutorial we will be predicting the injury level of car crashes based on data provided by police. We wil use two datasets from Montgomery County, Maryland. The data is collected via the Automated Crash Reporting System (ACRS). Specifically, we will use two datasets: Incidents Report: This dataset provides general information on the crash. Drivers Report: This dataset provides information on the drivers involved in the crash, including injury.
